
freeCodeCamp user stories :

ok    User Story: As an authenticated user, I can keep my polls and come back later to access them.
ok    User Story: As an authenticated user, I can share my polls with my friends.
ok    User Story: As an authenticated user, I can see the aggregate results of my polls.
ok    User Story: As an authenticated user, I can delete polls that I decide I don't want anymore.
ok    User Story: As an authenticated user, I can create a poll with any number of possible items.
ok    User Story: As an unauthenticated or authenticated user, I can see and vote on everyone's polls.
ok    User Story: As an unauthenticated or authenticated user, I can see the results of polls in chart form. (This could be implemented using Chart.js or Google Charts.)
ok    User Story: As an authenticated user, if I don't like the options on a poll, I can create a new option.

// mongodb how-to : https://www.mkyong.com/mongodb/how-to-create-database-or-collection-in-mongodb/


database [D]

    [D] votingdb

collections [C] and objects [O] with keys [K] (and values)

    [K] _id : automatically generated by mongodb (string)

    [C] users
        [O] user
            [K] authInfo ? (login, password)
            [K] username

    [C] polls
        [O] poll
            [K*] userid     // poll creator
            [K*] title      // poll title
            [K] info        // more info about poll
            [K] items       // array of items
                [O] item
                    [K] itemname
                    [K] votecount
                    [K] voternames  // ??? to forbbid multiple votes from same user (array or userids)

